# Shinu

**Shinu** is a blazing-fast, memory-safe media compression library written in Rust with Python . It supports compressing **images**, **videos**, **audio**, and **PDFs** with customizable quality settings.

## ğŸš€ Features

- ğŸ“· **Images** â€” JPEG, PNG, WebP, AVIF, BMP, TIFF, GIF, ICO
- ğŸï¸ **Videos** â€” MP4, AVI, MKV (via FFmpeg)
- ğŸµ **Audio** â€” MP3, WAV, OGG, etc. (via FFmpeg)
- ğŸ“„ **PDFs** â€” Compressed using Ghostscript
- ğŸ§  **Memory-safe**, **fast**, and built in Rust
- âœ… Per-media configurable compression settings
- ğŸ”Œ Easy integration into Python & FastAPI apps

---
## Install
```bash
pip install shinu
```

## Usage in Python
```python
from shinu import compress_file, CompressorConfig

config = CompressorConfig()
config.quality = 0.7
config.pdf_quality = "ebook"
config.image_format = "png"
config.image_colorspace = "rgb"
config.audio_bitrate = "128k"
config.video_crf = 28

output = compress_file("input.pdf", config)
print(output)
```
